HEADWORD: Adamical
<hw>A*dam"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to Adam, or
resembling him.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Adamic earth</b></col>, <cd>a name given to common red
clay, from a notion that <xex>Adam</xex> means <xex>red
earth</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adamite</ent>⟦br⟧
